article.headline: California 74, Oregon State 60
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. (AP) -- Kiki Williams scored a season-high 23
points and Jessica Lawson added 17 to help California defeat Oregon
State 74-60 Thursday night.

The Golden Bears (10-16, 4-13 Pac-10) won for only the second
time in their last 13 games, but they have been tough at home all
season. Nine of their 10 wins have come at Haas Pavilion.

Shannon Howell scored 21 points to lead Oregon State (6-21,
1-16), which has lost 11 of 12 and six in a row.

Cal trailed early before Kristin Iwanaga's three-point play gave
the Bears a 19-18 lead they didn't relinquish. That was part of a
19-2 run keyed by Iwanaga, who had eight points in two assists in
the spurt.

Iwanaga scored all 13 of her points in the first half as Cal
took a 38-22 lead.

The lead extended to 54-35 with 13:12 remaining in the game.
Oregon State managed to get within seven on Casey Bunn's layin with
2:22 left, but that was as close as it got.
